stylometry:
Transportation- is a problem that involves shipping a product directly from producer to customer (origin to destination) with no stops at warehouses in the middle. It involves capacity, demand, and production costs. Transshipment- is a problem that does involve middle points (warehouses) in between the origin and destination and also involves holding costs. Nodes are destinations throughout the network model, Arcs are represented by arrows and show the path of the flow, and Flows are the amount of product traveling through the arc. 

An example of transhipment would be the car production plants problem where they produce cars in 4 different cities and ship to 4 other cities but they have warehouses in 2 different cities along the way and it costs X amount to ship directly and Y amount to stop at a warehouse in between and you want to know what paths to take to minimize costs.
